{{Keralahistory}}{{Location|10.657175|76.118652}} [[File:Burial Cave at Eyyal DSC 0667.JPG|250px|thumb|right|Burial Cave at Eyyal, Thrissur District, kerala]] '''Eyyal Burial Cave''' is a [[prehistoric]] [[Megalith]] rock cut cave situated in [[Eyyal]], of [[Thrissur District]] of [[Kerala]]. The cave can be accessed from single entry and its chamber is circular. [[Archaeological Survey of India]] has declared this cave as centrally protected monument.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://asi.nic.in/asi_monu_alphalist_kerala.asp |title=Alphabetical List of Monuments - Kerala |publisher=ASI |accessdate=2014-11-16}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.asithrissurcircle.in/Monuments.html |title=BURIAL CAVE (Eyyal) |publisher=ASI Thrissur |accessdate=2014-11-16}}</ref>
