{{italics title}}{{Infobox book | name = The Family: The Real Story of the Bush Dynasty | image = The Family The Real Story of the Bush Dynasty.jpg | author = [[Kitty Kelley]] | language = English | country = United States | genre = Biography | published = 2004 ([[Doubleday (publisher)|Doubleday]]) | isbn = 978-0385503242 | pages = 736 | oclc = 56471745 | congress = E747 .K45 2004b }}
'''''The Family: The Real Story of the Bush Dynasty''''' is an unauthorized biography of the [[Bush family]] by the American [[investigative journalist]] [[Kitty Kelley]]. It was published on September 14, 2004, less than two months before the [[2004 US Presidential election]]. Reviews of the book were mixed, with some of the "accusations," according to ''[[The New York Times]]'', "[standing] up better than others."<ref name="NYT">{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2004/10/10/books/review/the-family-here-comes-the-son.html|title='The Family': Here Comes the Son|last=Widmer|first=Ted|date=2004-10-10|newspaper=The New York Times|access-date=2017-02-26|issn=0362-4331}}</ref>
Glynn Wilson, a free-lance journalist from [[Alabama]], sued Kelley for plagiarism claiming passages from the book have the exact wording as his online article.<ref name="Wilson">{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2004/11/17/books/a-writer-is-suing-the-author-of-a-hit-book-on-the-bushes.html|title=A Writer Is Suing the Author of a Hit Book on the Bushes|last=Wyatt|first=Edward|date=2004-11-17|newspaper=The New York Times|access-date=2017-02-26|issn=0362-4331}}</ref>
