'''Xenography''' is knowledge of a foreign language.<ref Name="Cobbett">{{cite book |title= A new French & English dictionary |last= Cobbett |first= William |authorlink= William Cobbett |coauthors= |year= 1833 |publisher= Mills, Jowett & Mills |location= Original from the University of Michigan |isbn= |page= 408 |pages= |url= https://books.google.com/books?id=BfjUAAAAMAAJ&pg=PA408&dq=Xenography}}</ref>
In [[Spiritualism]], writing in a language which is unknown to the writer.<ref Name="Post">{{cite book |title= Communicating with the Beyond: A Practical Handbook of Spiritualism |last= Post |first= Eric G. |authorlink= |coauthors= |year= 2006 |publisher= Kessinger Publishing |location= |isbn= 1-4253-7500-6 |page= 109 |pages= |url= https://books.google.com/books?id=ioUB71Ae_3gC&pg=PA109&dq=Xenography}}</ref> It is similar, but not the same as, [[xenoglossy]] and [[xenolalia]]. {{Citation needed|date=July 2009}}
